    {
      "id": "networks-dns-resolution",
      "name": "DNS Resolution",
      "description": "DNS resolution maps a hostname to an IP address through a hierarchy: the resolver first checks its cache, and on a miss queries the root server, which refers it to the TLD server and then to the authoritative name server that returns the record; the answer is cached with its TTL before being returned.",
